---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="L1 Help Desk — Build Crystal"
  description="A Crystal L1 help desk worker clears the ticket queue overnight, handles password resets and common L1 tickets, and escalates what it can't close. ~$2,500/mo. Ready in 3-5 days."
  active="workers"
>
  <article class="worker">
    <div class="frame">

      <!-- HEAD -->
      <header class="worker-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Available for hire</p>
        <h1>L1 Help Desk.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          A virtual employee for your ticket queue. Works overnights and weekends, handles password
          resets and common L1 work, closes what it can close, and routes what it can't to L2 with
          clean notes.
        </p>
        <div class="head-meta">
          <div><strong>~$2,500 / mo</strong><span>~50% of the human hire</span></div>
          <div><strong>24 / 7</strong><span>queue coverage, no SLA gaps</span></div>
          <div><strong>3&ndash;5 days</strong><span>from call to live</span></div>
          <div><strong>28 days</strong><span>free pilot</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="head-ctas">
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary" data-hire data-role="l1-helpdesk">Hire L1 help desk</a>
          <a href="#details" class="btn btn-secondary">See what it does</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- ROW 1: WHAT IT DOES  |  EXAMPLE TICKET -->
      <section class="paired-section" id="details">
        <div class="paired-cols">
          <div class="pc-body">
            <p class="section-label">What it does</p>
            <h2>A Crystal L1 worker, day to day.</h2>
            <ul class="does">
              <li>Works the ticket queue overnight, weekends, and holidays.</li>
              <li>Handles password resets, MFA resets, access requests, and common L1 tickets.</li>
              <li>Closes what it can close. Routes what it can't with clean notes for the L2 picking it up.</li>
              <li>Escalates out-of-scope tickets to a named engineer with full context.</li>
              <li>Logs every action and every tool call. Fully auditable.</li>
              <li>Every correction sticks &mdash; the same ticket doesn't stump it twice.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="sub-block">
              <h3>What it doesn't do.</h3>
              <p>
                Anything requiring on-site hands &mdash; hardware swaps, cable runs, physical presence.
                Anything outside the scope you define at setup; the worker is scoped to respect the line.
              </p>
              <p>
                Anything customer-facing before you're ready. Most L1 deployments start internal-only,
                working tickets from your staff, not your end customers, until you're confident.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="fit-card">
              <p class="fit-label">Typical fit</p>
              <ul class="fit-list">
                <li>MSP with L2 getting paged for L1 at 11 PM</li>
                <li>Internal IT team at 100+ person company</li>
                <li>SLA breaches overnight or on weekends</li>
                <li>L1 hire turnover inside 18 months is the norm</li>
                <li>Open to narrow, scoped pilot before broader rollout</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="pc-body">
            <p class="section-label">Example ticket</p>
            <h2>What a real L1 ticket looks like.</h2>
            <p class="section-sub">Actual L1 pattern. Names fictional &mdash; your worker is trained on your PSA, procedures, and escalation tree.</p>

            <div class="transcript">
              <div class="t-meta">Ticket #4872 &middot; ConnectWise &middot; 03:14 AM</div>

              <div class="ticket-msg from-user">
                <span class="who">james.lin@acme.co</span>
                <span class="when">03:14 AM</span>
                <p><strong>VPN not connecting</strong></p>
                <p>I'm locked out of the VPN and I need the file server for an early meeting. Getting "Authentication failed" on Cisco AnyConnect.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="ticket-msg from-worker">
                <span class="who">Crystal &middot; L1</span>
                <span class="when">03:15 AM</span>
                <p>Hey James &mdash; your VPN account got flagged after some failed login attempts yesterday. I've cleared the lock. Try again and let me know.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="ticket-msg from-user">
                <span class="who">james.lin@acme.co</span>
                <span class="when">03:17 AM</span>
                <p>Worked. Thanks.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="ticket-msg from-worker">
                <span class="who">Crystal &middot; L1</span>
                <span class="when">03:17 AM</span>
                <p>Anytime. One note &mdash; you had three failed attempts from a different IP earlier tonight. I'm flagging this ticket for the daytime team to review for security.</p>
              </div>

              <div class="t-footer">
                <span class="tf-tag">Resolved &mdash; 3 min</span>
                <span class="tf-tag">AD account unlocked</span>
                <span class="tf-tag">Flagged for security review</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ROW 2: WORKS WITH  |  MATH -->
      <section class="paired-section">
        <div class="paired-cols">
          <div class="pc-body">
            <p class="section-label">Works with</p>
            <h2>Your existing stack.</h2>
            <table class="def-table">
              <tbody>
                <tr><th>PSA / Ticketing</th><td>ConnectWise &middot; Autotask &middot; Freshservice &middot; Halo (planned)</td></tr>
                <tr><th>RMM</th><td>Kaseya &middot; NinjaRMM (planned) &middot; Datto</td></tr>
                <tr><th>Directory / SSO</th><td>Entra ID &middot; Okta &middot; Google Workspace</td></tr>
                <tr><th>Comms</th><td>Slack &middot; Teams &middot; Email</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p class="section-footnote">
              Don't see yours? Tell us on the working session. We'll build the connector or tell you it's not a fit.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="pc-body">
            <p class="section-label">The math</p>
            <h2>What it costs.</h2>
            <table class="def-table">
              <tbody>
                <tr><th>Market salary (loaded)</th><td>~$60,000 / yr</td></tr>
                <tr><th>Crystal L1 worker</th><td>~$2,500 / mo</td></tr>
                <tr><th>Coverage</th><td>24 / 7 (overnights &amp; weekends)</td></tr>
                <tr><th>Setup time</th><td>3&ndash;5 business days</td></tr>
                <tr><th>Free trial</th><td>28 days, no card</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p class="section-footnote">
              Included: worker, build-out, training, integrations, corrections, maintenance, updates. Not included: your Anthropic API bill &mdash; you own it, we don't resell it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section class="faq-section">
        <p class="section-label">Questions we get</p>
        <h2>Real questions, honest answers.</h2>
        <div class="faq">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What's your close rate?</h3>
            <p>Depends on the scope you define at setup. A narrow L1 scope (password resets, access requests, common faults) closes 70&ndash;85% unassisted. Anything outside that scope routes to L2 with notes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What if it confidently answers wrong?</h3>
            <p>Biggest risk in L1. We scope tightly at setup and monitor for confidence drift. Corrections go into the knowledge base and stick. Every action is logged &mdash; fully auditable.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Can it page on-call for real incidents?</h3>
            <p>Yes, with rules you define. Out-of-scope or high-severity tickets route directly to the named engineer, skipping the queue. The worker never sits on something it shouldn't.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="worker-cta">
        <h3>Hiring L1 help desk?</h3>
        <p>Book a 15-minute working session. We'll walk through your current queue and show you what one of ours would do with it.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary" data-hire data-role="l1-helpdesk">Book a working session</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .worker { padding: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem) 0 clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem); }
  .worker-head { max-width: 60rem; margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); }
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .worker-head h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.8vw, 3.5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .worker-head .lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.6vw, 1.2rem);
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .head-meta {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(10rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .head-meta strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .head-meta span { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--ink-muted); }
  .head-ctas { display: flex; gap: 0.6rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  .section-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem;
  }
  .section-sub {
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    max-width: 52ch;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .section-footnote {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Paired column sections */
  .paired-section {
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .paired-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .paired-cols { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.5rem; }
  }
  .pc-body h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.2vw, 1.7rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .pc-body .sub-block {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.75rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .pc-body .sub-block h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .pc-body .sub-block p {
    margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .pc-body .sub-block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .pc-body .fit-card { margin-top: 2rem; }

  /* Single-column section */
  .worker-section {
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    max-width: 60rem;
  }
  .worker-section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.4vw, 1.8rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .worker-section p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    max-width: 62ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .worker-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  /* "Does" list */
  .does {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .does li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.7rem;
  }
  .does li::before {
    content: "";
    width: 5px; height: 5px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-top: 0.6em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  /* Transcript (ticket style) */
  .transcript {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }
  .t-meta {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.65rem;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--rule);
  }
  .ticket-msg {
    padding: 0.7rem 0.9rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--paper-2);
  }
  .ticket-msg.from-worker {
    background: var(--accent-wash);
    border-left-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .ticket-msg .who {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-right: 0.55rem;
  }
  .ticket-msg .when {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-family: var(--mono);
  }
  .ticket-msg p {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  .ticket-msg p strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 600; }
  .t-footer {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--rule);
  }
  .tf-tag {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #e5f2ea;
    color: var(--ok);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  /* Two-up (doesn't do + fit) */
  .two-up {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .two-up { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .fit-card {
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    align-self: start;
  }
  .fit-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .fit-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .fit-list li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }
  .fit-list li::before {
    content: "✓";
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  /* Def table shared by works + math */
  .def-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.93rem;
  }
  .def-table th, .def-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.7rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    vertical-align: top;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .def-table tr:first-child th,
  .def-table tr:first-child td {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .def-table th {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    width: 38%;
    padding-right: 1rem;
  }
  .def-table td { color: var(--ink); }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section {
    padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .faq-section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.4vw, 1.8rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .faq {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(18rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    max-width: 60rem;
  }
  .faq-item {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }
  .faq-item h3 {
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .faq-item p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .worker-cta {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding: 2rem 2.25rem;
    background: var(--accent-wash);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    max-width: 56rem;
  }
  .worker-cta h3 { margin: 0 0 0.4rem; font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .worker-cta p { margin: 0 0 1rem; color: var(--ink-2); }
</style>
